<legend id="HAS">High Avail Sync</legend>

<table class="table hovered">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th colspan="2">
                <label>State Synchronization Settings</label>
            </th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <label>Synchronize States</label>
            </td>
            <td>
                <input id="NewSynchronizeStates" type="checkbox" />
                <p id="UpdateSynchronizeStates" class="button bg-anthilla-green">Apply</p>
                <br />
                This setting should be enabled on all members of a failover group
                <p>NOTE: Clicking save will force a configuration sync if it is enabled! </p>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <label>Synchronize Interface</label>
            </td>
            <td>
                <input id="NewSynchronizeInterface" type="checkbox" />
                <p id="UpdateSynchronizeInterface" class="button bg-anthilla-green">Apply</p>
                <br />
                If Synchronize States is enabled, it will utilize this interface for communication
                <p>NOTE: We recommend setting this to a interface other than LAN! A dedicated interface works the best </p>
                <p>NOTE: You must define a IP on each machine participating in this failover group </p>
                <p>NOTE: You must have an IP assigned to the interface on any participating sync nodes </p>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <label>Synchronize Peer IP</label>
            </td>
            <td>
                <input id="NewSynchronizePeerIP" type="text" />
                <p id="UpdateSynchronizePeerIP" class="button bg-anthilla-green">Apply</p>
                <br />
                Setting this option will force antd to synchronize its state table to this IP address. The default is directed multicast
            </td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
